Date:  0/0/1952
Source:  Chatham Islands
Author:  RICHARDS
Vol / Page:  85
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Prion ... vittatus</i> ... These tiny birds are light grey above; ... The blue bill is very wide and edges of the upper mandible turn upwards. ... They breed on the Chathams. There are three sorts of blue billies as they are locally called. ... Whalebirds, Blue Billies.
Notes:

